{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"A plugin whose manifest is missing a required field is rejected before any code from that plugin is executed.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is loader wiring between manifest validation and module import. The test must prove validation happens first and blocks entry-module execution; a pure validator unit test cannot catch accidental early import. Rejected higher levels: behavior text is only local plugin-dir loading with no subprocess/network/external API (so not System), and no AI step (so not Agentic/Workflow).","test_description":"Create a temp plugin directory with one plugin whose `manifest.json` omits a required field and whose entry module has a visible side effect (e.g., writes a marker file or toggles a shared flag on import). Run the real loader against that directory and assert: (1) loader reports manifest validation failure, (2) side effect never occurs, (3) plugin `onLoad` is never called.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When plugin A declares a dependency on plugin B, plugin B's `onLoad` hook is called before plugin A's.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is module-handoff/state-order behavior (manifest dependency graph -> resolved order -> hook invocation order). A unit test of topological sort alone misses wiring bugs in hook dispatch. Rejected higher levels: no required subprocess/OS contract beyond in-process loading (not System) and no model output dependence (not Agentic/Workflow).","test_description":"Set up two real test plugins in a temp directory: A depends on B; each `onLoad` appends its name to a shared in-memory/log sink. Run loader and assert recorded order is `[B, A]` and both hooks executed exactly once.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.82,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"When two plugins each declare a dependency on the other, the loader reports the cycle and loads neither.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Real failure appears at interaction of dependency resolution and load executor: cycle detection must prevent any plugin initialization. Unit-level graph test alone does not verify loader suppresses loads. Rejected higher levels: behavior concerns local dependency metadata only, with no subprocess/network/external API and no AI steps.","test_description":"Create plugins A and B where each depends on the other; give both entry modules and `onLoad` hooks observable side effects. Execute loader and assert: (1) cycle error is reported with A/B, (2) neither entry-module side effect occurs, (3) neither `onLoad` is invoked.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.84,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A plugin's `onLoad` hook is only invoked after the plugin's entry module has been imported and executed.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Behavior is an ordering guarantee across loader stages (import/execute module -> invoke exported hook). It needs real module import semantics plus loader orchestration, not just one function. Rejected higher levels: no external process/network/OS event requirement beyond normal in-process module loading; no AI dependence.","test_description":"Build one test plugin whose entry module sets `initialized=true` as import side effect and exports `onLoad` that asserts `initialized===true` and records call time/order. Run loader and assert `onLoad` runs only after import side effect is visible; fail if hook can run before module execution.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.85,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When a plugin throws an error during its `onLoad` hook, the loader continues initializing the remaining plugins that do not depend on it.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is error-propagation and dependency-aware continuation across components (hook runner + dependency graph + scheduler). Unit-testing try/catch logic alone misses cross-plugin continuation rules. Rejected higher levels: behavior does not require subprocess/network/external API behavior, and has no model-output dependency or multi-agent sequence.","test_description":"Create plugins: `core` (throws in `onLoad`), `independent` (no dependency on `core`), and `child` (depends on `core`). Run loader and assert: (1) `core` error is reported, (2) `independent` still loads and its `onLoad` executes, (3) `child` does not load because dependency failed.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.86,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}}]}
